Nature's most spectacular light show via @imikegraphics. 💫 As we've fully settled into August, the much-awaited season of the Aurora Borealis in Lapland is lingering in our minds, as it usually spans from mid-August until early April. 

The most traditional ways to go Aurora spotting include snowshoeing, cross-country skiing, or snowmobiling. But if you prefer a little more comfort, booking a stay in a glass igloo is also an excellent option. 🇫🇮

From 1-8, which is your favorite photo? 💙

📸 @imikegraphics

The Eternal Couple
.
Saaya and Cleopatra have been courting since 4 years now and whenever they are together it’s a sight to behold. The forest comes alive as they trot nonchalantly in his fabled kingdom. Usually in the courting pairs generally it is the Male who takes charge and moves around with the female following close behind. But with this couple it was definitely Cleo who was in charge while the Panther followed. 

Photos by @mithunhphotography
